n 2012. The project promises to be the inverse of New York&#39;s High Line.</p>  <p>Barasch has long known that he wanted to make a difference, but for years, wasn&#39;t quite sure how to go about doing that. Before he left his job to work fultime on the Lowline, he led strategic partnerships at PopTech; held multiple roles at Google; and worked in small business development in New York City government. He also consulted for UNICEF in Nairobi and with the 9/11 Survivors&rsquo; Fund in Washington DC. He began his career at the World Affairs Council in San Francisco, co-producing the weekly NPR show &ldquo;It&rsquo;s Your World.&rdquo;</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Dan Barasch","tags":["New York","architecture","cities"],"title":"A park underneath the hustle and bustle of New York City","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":889903}]}
